#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:3
msgid "Change Replica Set to WiredTiger"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:7
msgid ""
"Starting in version 3.2, WiredTiger is the default storage engine for "
"MongoDB."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:10
msgid ""
"This tutorial gives an overview of changing the storage engine of a "
"member of a :term:`replica set` to :ref:`WiredTiger <storage-"
"wiredtiger>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:15
msgid "Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:17
msgid ""
"Replica sets can have members with different storage engines. As such, "
"you can update members to use the WiredTiger storage engine in a rolling "
"fashion."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:24
msgid "MongoDB 3.6 and PSA 3-member Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:26
msgid ""
"Starting in MongoDB 3.6, :readconcern:`\"majority\"` read concern, "
"available for WiredTiger, is enabled by default. However, for **MongoDB "
"3.6.1-3.6.x**, if you have a three-member replica set with a primary-"
"secondary-arbiter (PSA) architecture, you can disable "
":readconcern:`\"majority\"` read concern. Disabling "
":readconcern:`\"majority\"` for a three member PSA architecture avoids "
"possible cache-pressure build up."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:34
msgid ""
"The procedure below disables :readconcern:`\"majority\"` read concern for"
" MongoDB 3.6.1-3.6.x PSA architecture by including "
":option:`--enableMajorityReadConcern false <mongod "
"--enableMajorityReadConcern>`. If you are running a MongoDB 3.6.0 PSA "
"architecture, first upgrade to the latest 3.6 version in order to disable"
" this read concern."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:43
msgid ""
"Disabling :readconcern:`\"majority\"` read concern disables support for "
":doc:`/changeStreams`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:46
msgid ""
"For more information on PSA architecture and read concern "
":readconcern:`\"majority\"`, see :ref:`3.6-disable-read-concern-"
"majority`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:50
msgid "MongoDB 3.0 or Greater"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/includes/fact-wiredtiger-minimum-version.rst:1
msgid ""
"You must be using MongoDB version 3.0 or greater in order to use the "
"WiredTiger storage engine. If using an earlier MongoDB version, you must "
"upgrade your MongoDB version before proceeding to change your storage "
"engine. To upgrade your MongoDB version, refer to the appropriate version"
" of the manual."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:58
msgid "Default Bind to Localhost"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/includes/fact-default-bind-ip-change.rst:1
msgid ""
"Starting with MongoDB 3.6, MongoDB binaries, :binary:`~bin.mongod` and "
":binary:`~bin.mongos`, bind to ``localhost`` by default. From MongoDB "
"versions 2.6 to 3.4, only the binaries from the official MongoDB RPM (Red"
" Hat, CentOS, Fedora Linux, and derivatives) and DEB (Debian, Ubuntu, and"
" derivatives) packages would bind to ``localhost`` by default. To learn "
"more about this change, see :ref:`3.6-bind_ip-compatibility`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:65
msgid "XFS and WiredTiger"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:67
msgid ""
"With the WiredTiger storage engine, using XFS for data bearing nodes is "
"recommended on Linux. For more information, see :ref:`prod-notes-linux-"
"file-system`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:72
msgid "Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:74
msgid ""
"To update a member to WiredTiger, the procedure removes a member's data, "
"starts :binary:`~bin.mongod` with WiredTiger, and performs an "
":doc:`initial sync </tutorial/resync-replica-set-member>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:80
msgid ""
"To update all members of the replica set to use WiredTiger, update the "
"members in a rolling manner. That is, update, one by one, all "
":term:`secondary` members first. Then, once all the secondary members "
"have been updated, :method:`step down <rs.stepDown()>` the "
":term:`primary`, and update that stepped-down member."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/tutorial/change-replica-set-wiredtiger.txt:86
msgid ""
"If you are running a MongoDB 3.6.0 three-member PSA architecture and wish"
" to disable :readconcern:`\"majority\"` read concern, upgrade first to "
"the latest 3.6 version."
msgstr ""

